From: bluecat <lmhtq1991@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 28 May 2026 13:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Phase C-6 fix #7: mov(Rd, zr) special case for patch 0088

Patch 0088 changed `mov(Reg, Reg)` to use `add(Rd, Rn, #0)` on
CHERI to preserve cap tags. But that broke the `mov(Rd, zr)` case
because HotSpot encodes the zero register `zr` as Register #32
(distinct from `sp` at #33 and the explicit `r31_sp` at #31), and
`Assembler::add` doesn't translate #32 → the bits[9:5] Rn field.
Result: emit field overflow when generating native-method entry
stubs that issue `mov(rscratch, zr)` (one of many).

Diagnosis: with patch 0087's SIGPROT diagnostic + patch 0088
unblocking forward_exception, the JVM now reached
TemplateInterpreterGenerator::generate_native_entry and hit a
NEW assembler guarantee:
  [C6f] OVERFLOW val=32(0x20) msb=9 lsb=5 nbits=5 insn_so_far=0x91000016
                    ^^                                      ^^^^^^^^^^^
                    Rn=32                              ADD partial encoding
  ra1 = generate_native_entry
        templateInterpreterGenerator_aarch64.cpp:1145
which decodes as: trying to encode `ADD Xd, X32, #0` — a register
beyond the 5-bit valid range.

Register encoding from register_aarch64.hpp:120-122:
  r31_sp  = (31)   // real reg 31 — used where context picks ZR or SP
  zr      = (32)   // pseudo, gets translated by aware encoders
  sp      = (33)   // pseudo, gets translated by aware encoders

The original `orr(Rd, zr, Rn)` worked because `orr`'s encoder
recognizes zr and emits register #31 with the ORR ZR variant.
`Assembler::add` translates `sp` but not `zr`.

Fix: special-case `Rn == zr` in mov(Reg, Reg) — fall back to the
classic `orr Rd, ZR, ZR` pattern, which is the correct semantic
anyway (mov-from-zr means "zero out Rd", which is integer-zero,
not cap-preserving — we WANT the tag clear).

Effect: with this patch, JVM init progresses further into
String::<clinit> execution. Hits next blocker at PC 0x428b4138
(another stub-blob fault, presumably yet another cap-truncating
sequence). To be diagnosed next session.

diff --git a/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/macroAssembler_aarch64.hpp b/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/macroAssembler_aarch64.hpp
--- a/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/macroAssembler_aarch64.hpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/macroAssembler_aarch64.hpp
@@ -239,6 +239,15 @@
       Assembler::add(Rd, Rn, 0U);
+    } else if (Rn == zr) {
+      // Move zero into Rd; this is intentionally an integer-zero
+      // (NOT cap-preserving) since the source is the zero register.
+      // Must use orr here because Assembler::add doesn't translate
+      // zr (encoded as #32 in HotSpot to disambiguate from sp/r31_sp);
+      // passing zr to add would emit register #32 in the 5-bit Rn
+      // field, overflowing. orr's encoder handles zr correctly.
+      orr(Rd, zr, Rn);
     } else {
 #ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
       Assembler::add(Rd, Rn, 0U);
 #else
       orr(Rd, zr, Rn);
 #endif
     }
